      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2017-05-25</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Truck, Trailer, and Transport Efficiency Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill removes trailers that do not emit greenhouse gases in connection with a propulsion system from the scope of the final rule titled &quot;Greenhouse Gas Emissions and Fuel Efficiency Standards for Medium- and Heavy-Duty Engines and Vehicles--Phase 2.&quot; The Environmental Protection Agency and the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration jointly issued the rule, which created fuel consumption standards and carbon dioxide emission standards for heavy-duty vehicles (e.g., tractors, trucks, vans, and vocational vehicles), on October 25, 2016.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <updateDate>2017-05-25T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-01-25T19:31:25Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
        </item>
